In Figure \ref{cc2} we singled out the energy region of the pygmy resonance and we plot the results of our calculations for two different bombarding energies: 100 MeV/nucleon and 2 GeV/nucleon, with the same notation as in Figure \ref{cc1}. The coupling effects change dramatically. At the lower energy the influence of the giant resonances is to increase appreciably the response in the energy region of the PDR, while at the higher energy the effect of coupling is much smaller and the tendency is to slightly decrease the PDR excitation cross section. This result is expected because at  energies around 100 MeV/nucleon the E2 field is dominant, with an appreciable increase of  the excitation of the GQR and a consequently strong feedback to the PDR via subsequent E1 transitions.

